#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:1
msgid "MSProbe Debugging Guide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:3
msgid "Introduction to MSProbe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:5
msgid ""
"MSProbe is a debugging tool for AI models that diagnoses accuracy anomalies "
"and numerical errors during model training and inference. It captures and "
"monitors intermediate data (feature maps, weights, activations, layer "
"outputs) and contextual metadata (prompts, tensor dtypes, hardware "
"configuration), and supports visual analysis to systematically trace the "
"root cause of accuracy degradation or numerical errors (e.g., NaN/Inf, "
"output drift, mismatched predictions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:11
msgid "Basic Details"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:13
msgid "Background Concepts: MSProbe Dumping Levels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:15
msgid ""
"MSProbe supports three accuracy levels for data dumping, each for different "
"debugging needs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:17
msgid ""
"**L0**: Dumps tensors/statistics at the **module level** and generates "
"`construct.json` (for network structure reconstruction in visualization). "
"Requires passing a model/submodule handle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:19
msgid ""
"**L1**: Dumps tensors/statistics at the **torch API level**, suitable for "
"fine-grained API-level numerical checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:20
msgid ""
"**mix**: Combines L0 + L1, ideal for scenarios that require both **graph "
"reconstruction** and **numerical comparison**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:22
msgid "Prerequisites: Install MSProbe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:24
msgid "Install MSProbe with pip:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:26
msgid "pip install mindstudio-probe --pre\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:30
msgid "Key Configuration Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:32
msgid ""
"MSProbe uses a JSON configuration file for customized data dumping. All core "
"parameters are listed in the table below, with the default JSON "
"configuration provided for reference."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:35
msgid "Configuration Parameter Table"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "Field"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "Required"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`task`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Type of dump task. Common PyTorch values include `\"statistics\"` and "
"`\"tensor\"`. A statistics task collects tensor statistics (mean, variance, "
"max, min, etc.) while a tensor task captures arbitrary tensors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "Yes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`dump_path`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Directory where dump results are stored. When omitted, `MSProbe` uses its "
"default path."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "No"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`rank`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Ranks to sample. An empty list collects every rank. For single-card tasks "
"you must set this field to `[]`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`step`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "Token iteration(s) to sample. An empty list means every iteration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`level`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Dump level string (`\"L0\"`, `\"L1\"`, or `\"mix\"`). `L0` targets `nn."
"Module`, `L1` targets `torch.api`, and `mix` collects both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`async_dump`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Whether to enable asynchronous dump (supported for PyTorch `statistics`/"
"`tensor` tasks). Defaults to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`scope`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Customize the scope of dump. Provide two module or API names that follow the "
"tool's naming convention to lock a range, only data between the two names "
"will be dumped. An empty list dumps every module or torch API.<br/><br/"
">Examples:<br/>`\"scope\": [\"Module.conv1.Conv2d.forward.0\", \"Module.fc2."
"Linear.forward.0\"]`<br/>`\"scope\": [\"Tensor.add.0.forward\", \"Functional."
"square.2.forward\"]`<br/><br/>The `level` setting determines what can be "
"provided—modules when `level=L0`, APIs when `level=L1`, and either modules "
"or APIs when `level=mix`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:45
#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:46
msgid "<br/>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid "`list`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:0
msgid ""
"Customize dump list, only dumps elements from the list. An empty list dumps "
"every module or torch API. Options include:<br/><br/>&#738226;Supply the "
"full names of specific APIs in PyTorch pynative scenarios to only dump those "
"APIs. Example: `\"list\": [\"Tensor.permute.1.forward\", \"Tensor."
"transpose.2.forward\", \"Torch.relu.3.backward\"]`.<br/>&#738226;When "
"`level=mix`, you can provide module names so that the dump expands to "
"everything produced while the module is running. Example: `\"list\": "
"[\"Module.module.language_model.encoder.layers.0.mlp.ParallelMlp."
"forward.0\"]`.<br/>&#738226;Provide a substring such as `\"list\": "
"[\"relu\"]` to dump every API whose name contains the substring. When "
"`level=mix`, modules whose names contain the substring are also expanded."
msgstr ""

