msgid ""
"**Note**: When MSProbe is enabled, cuda graph is "
"disabled(disable_cuda_graph=True) because MSProbe only supports dump in "
"eager mode, warmup is disabled(skip_server_warmup=True) because there is no "
"need to dump data for this stage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:97
msgid "End-to-End Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:99
msgid ""
"MSProbe’s full debugging workflow follows **Enable → Collect Data → "
"Visualize → Analyze Root Cause**. Below is a common E2E example for SGLang-"
"based model inference debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:102
msgid "Example : Advanced Debugging with Custom Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:104
msgid ""
"Suitable for targeted debugging (e.g., only collect statistics data for "
"specific ranks/steps, enable mix level for graph reconstruction + numerical "
"comparison) and root cause analysis via **problem vs. benchmark comparison**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:107
msgid "Step 1: Enable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:108
msgid "Prepare Custom Configuration JSON"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:110
msgid ""
"Create `msprobe-config.json` (dump statistics data for rank0/1, step0/1, mix "
"level):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:112
msgid ""
"{\n"
"  \"task\": \"statistics\",\n"
"  \"dump_path\": \"./problem_dump\",\n"
"  \"rank\": [\n"
"    0,\n"
"    1\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"step\": [\n"
"    0,\n"
"    1\n"
"  ],\n"
"  \"level\": \"mix\",\n"
"  \"async_dump\": false,\n"
"  \"statistics\": {\n"
"    \"scope\": [],\n"
"    \"list\": [],\n"
"    \"data_mode\": [\n"
"      \"all\"\n"
"    ],\n"
"    \"summary_mode\": \"statistics\"\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:137
msgid "Enable MSProbe with Custom Configuration in SGLang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:139
msgid ""
"Launch the SGLang server and specify the configuration file path with `--"
"msprobe-dump-config`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:141
msgid ""
"python3 -m sglang.launch_server \\\n"
" --model-path Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct \\\n"
" --host 127.0.0.1 \\\n"
" --port 1027 \\\n"
" --msprobe-dump-config /home/msprobe-config.json\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:148
msgid "Step 2: Collect Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:149
msgid "Collect Dump Data for Problem & Benchmark Sides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:151
msgid ""
"Send normal inference requests to trigger model running (MSProbe "
"automatically collects data during request processing):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:153
msgid ""
"curl -H \"Content-type: application/json\" \\\n"
" -X POST \\\n"
" -d '{\n"
"     \"model\": \"Qwen/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct\",\n"
"     \"messages\": [\n"
"         {\n"
"             \"role\": \"user\",\n"
"             \"content\": \"Hello, my name is\"\n"
"         }\n"
"     ],\n"
"     \"max_tokens\": 10\n"
" }' \\\n"
" http://127.0.0.1:1027/v1/chat/completions\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:169
msgid ""
"**Problem side**: Run the above SGLang server (with the accuracy/numerical "
"issue) and send inference request; dump data is saved to `./problem_dump`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:171
msgid ""
"**Benchmark side**: Launch a normal SGLang server (without the issue, e.g., "
"stable framework version/operator) with the **same custom configuration** "
"and send the **same inference request**; rename the dump directory to `./"
"bench_dump`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:175
msgid ""
"**Key Requirement**: Problem and benchmark dumps must use the same inputs "
"and sampling points (rank/step) for valid comparison."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:178
msgid "Check Generated Dump Files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:180
msgid ""
"Dump files are saved to `./problem_dump` and `./bench_dump` you defined and "
"include core files for subsequent analysis:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:182
msgid ""
"`dump.json`: Records tensor metadata of APIs and modules (dtype, shape, min/"
"max/mean, L2 norm, `requires_grad`, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:183
msgid "`stack.json`: Logs call stack information of APIs and modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:184
msgid ""
"`construct.json`: hierarchical structure description, required for "
"visualization, its content is not empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:186
msgid "Step 3: Visualize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:187
msgid "Visualize Problem vs. Benchmark Comparison (Multi-Rank)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:189
msgid ""
"Generate a multi-rank comparison visualization file (mix level generates "
"`construct.json` for graph reconstruction):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:191
msgid ""
"msprobe graph_visualize -tp ./problem_dump/step0 -gp ./bench_dump/step0 -o ./"
"graph_output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:195
msgid "`-tp`: Path to problem-side dump data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:196
msgid "`-gp`: Path to benchmark-side dump data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:197
msgid "`-o`: Output directory for visualization files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:199
msgid ""
"If you want overflow check (for NaN/Inf detection), please specify the "
"parameter `-oc`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:201
msgid ""
"msprobe graph_visualize -tp ./problem_dump/step0 -gp ./bench_dump/step0 -o ./"
"graph_output -oc\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:205
msgid ""
"After the comparison or build task finishes, a `compare_{timestamp}.vis.db` "
"file is created under `graph_output`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:207
msgid "Launch TensorBoard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:209
msgid "Start TensorBoard:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:210
msgid "tensorboard --logdir ./graph_output --bind_all --port 6006\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:213
msgid "Step 4: Analyze Root Cause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:214
msgid "Locate Root Cause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:216
msgid "Root Cause Analysis in TensorBoard:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:217
msgid ""
"Divergent nodes (with accuracy/numerical differences) are highlighted in "
"**red** (darker red = larger difference)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:218
msgid ""
"Click on divergent nodes to view detailed tensor data (inputs/outputs, "
"parameters) and API/module call stacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:219
msgid ""
"Use the **search/filter** function to quickly locate key layers/APIs (e.g., "
"\"relu\", \"conv\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:220
msgid ""
"Switch between ranks/steps via the UI to check cross-rank/cross-step "
"divergence."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:221
msgid ""
"Check the **overflow check** tab for NaN/Inf values in specific nodes (the "
"direct cause of numerical instability)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:223
msgid "Verify the Root Cause"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:225
msgid ""
"After locating the divergent node (e.g., a specific Conv layer or torch API "
"with abnormal tensor values), verify by:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:227
msgid ""
"Narrowing the dump scope to this node (via `scope`/`list` in the "
"configuration file) for fine-grained data collection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:228
msgid ""
"Modifying the problematic layer/API (e.g., replacing the operator, adjusting "
"the dtype) and re-running the debugging workflow to confirm the issue is "
"resolved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:231
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:233
msgid "No Dump Files Generated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:235
msgid ""
"To confirm if MSProbe is installed, use `pip show mindstudio_probe` to "
"troubleshoot. If it is installed, the MSProbe version information will be "
"printed. If it is confirmed that it has not been installed, please use `pip "
"install mindstudio-probe --pre` for installation;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:238
msgid ""
"Confirm the `--msprobe-dump-config` parameter points to the **correct JSON "
"file path**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:240
msgid "Dump Files Are Too Large (Excessive Data)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:242
msgid ""
"Start with `task: \"statistics\"` instead of `\"tensor\"` to collect only "
"tensor statistics (avoids raw tensor dump);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:243
msgid ""
"Narrow the dump range with the `scope` field (specify start/end module/API);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:244
msgid ""
"Filter dump targets with the `list` field (only dump specific modules/APIs "
"or substrings);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:245
msgid "Sample specific `rank` and `step` (avoid dumping all ranks/iterations)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:247
msgid "TensorBoard Visualization Fails"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:249
msgid ""
"Confirm `construct.json` is not empty (requires `level: L0` or `mix` – L1 "
"does not generate graph files);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:250
msgid ""
"Check that the `-tp` (problem dump) and `-gp` (benchmark dump) paths point "
"to **valid rank/step subdirectories** ( e.g., `srep0/rank0`);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:252
msgid ""
"Ensure the MSProbe version is up-to-date (reinstall with `pip install "
"mindstudio-probe --pre --upgrade`);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:253
msgid ""
"Verify TensorBoard is installed and the `--logdir` parameter points to the "
"directory containing `.vis.db` files (not the file itself)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:256
msgid "Numerical Comparison Shows No Divergence But Model Accuracy Is Low"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:258
msgid ""
"Expand the dump `step` range (check more token iterations for late-stage "
"divergence);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:259
msgid ""
"Switch to `task: \"tensor\"` (statistics may mask subtle numerical "
"differences in raw tensor data);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:260
msgid ""
"Ensure the problem and benchmark dumps use **the same input data/hardware "
"configuration** (different inputs lead to invalid comparisons);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:262
msgid ""
"Use the `manual mapping` feature in TensorBoard (automatic mapping may miss "
"some nodes for custom models)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:266
msgid "Appendix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:268
msgid "Dump directory description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:270
msgid ""
"├── problem_dump or bench_dump\n"
"│   ├── step0\n"
"│   │   ├── rank0\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump_tensor_data\n"
"│   │   │   │    ├── Tensor.permute.1.forward.pt\n"
"│   │   │   │    ├── Functional.linear.5.backward.output.pt    # Format: "
"{api_type}.{api_name}.{call_count}.{forward/backward}.{input/output}."
"{arg_index}.\n"
"│   │   │   │    │                                              # arg_index "
"is the nth input or output of the API. If an input is a list, keep numbering "
"with decimals (e.g., 1.1 is the first element of the first argument).\n"
"│   │   │   │    ├── Module.conv1.Conv2d.forward.0.input.0.pt          # "
"Format: {Module}.{module_name}.{class_name}.{forward/backward}.{call_count}."
"{input/output}.{arg_index}.\n"
"│   │   │   │    ├── Module.conv1.Conv2d.forward.0.parameters.bias.pt  # "
"Module parameter data: {Module}.{module_name}.{class_name}.forward."
"{call_count}.parameters.{parameter_name}.\n"
"│   │   │   │    └── Module.conv1.Conv2d.parameters_grad.weight.pt     # "
"Module parameter gradients: {Module}.{module_name}.{class_name}."
"parameters_grad.{parameter_name}. Gradients do not include call_count "
"because the same gradient updates all invocations.\n"
"│   │   │   │                                                          # "
"When the `model` argument passed to dump is a List[torch.nn.Module] or "
"Tuple[torch.nn.Module], module-level data names also include the index "
"inside the list ({Module}.{index}.*), e.g., Module.0.conv1.Conv2d.forward.0."
"input.0.pt.\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump.json\n"
"│   │   │   ├── stack.json\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump_error_info.log\n"
"│   │   │   └── construct.json\n"
"│   │   ├── rank1\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump_tensor_data\n"
"│   │   │   │   └── ...\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump.json\n"
"│   │   │   ├── stack.json\n"
"│   │   │   ├── dump_error_info.log\n"
"│   │   │   └── construct.json\n"
"│   │   ├── ...\n"
"│   │   │\n"
"│   │   └── rank7\n"
"│   ├── step1\n"
"│   │   ├── ...\n"
"│   ├── step2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:301
msgid ""
"`rank`: Device ID. Each card writes its data to the corresponding `rank{ID}` "
"directory. In non-distributed scenarios the directory is simply named `rank`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:303
msgid "`dump_tensor_data`: Save the collected tensor data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:304
msgid ""
"`dump.json`: Statistics for the forward data of each API or module, "
"including names, dtype, shape, max, min, mean, L2 norm (square root of the "
"L2 variance), and CRC-32 when `summary_mode=\"md5\"`. See [dump.json file "
"description](#dumpjson-file-description) for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:307
msgid ""
"`dump_error_info.log`: Present only when the dump tool encountered an error "
"and records the failure log."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:308
msgid "`stack.json`: Call stacks for APIs/modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:309
msgid ""
"`construct.json`: Hierarchical structure description. Empty when `level=L1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:311
msgid "dump.json file description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:313
msgid "L0 level"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:315
msgid ""
"An L0 `dump.json` contains forward/backward I/O for modules together with "
"parameters and parameter gradients. Using PyTorch's `Conv2d` as an example, "
"the network code looks like:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:318
msgid ""
"`output = self.conv2(input)  # self.conv2 = torch.nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 5, "
"padding=2, bias=True)`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:320
msgid "`dump.json` contains the following entries:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:322
msgid ""
"`Module.conv2.Conv2d.forward.0`: Forward data of the module. `input_args` "
"represents positional inputs, `input_kwargs` represents keyword inputs, "
"`output` stores forward outputs, and `parameters` stores weights/biases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:324
msgid ""
"`Module.conv2.Conv2d.parameters_grad`: Parameter gradients (weight and bias)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:325
msgid ""
"`Module.conv2.Conv2d.backward.0`: Backward data of the module. `input` "
"represents gradients that flow into the module (gradients of the forward "
"outputs) and `output` represents gradients that flow out (gradients of the "
"module inputs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../developer_guide/msprobe_debugging_guide.md:329
msgid ""
"**Note**: When the `model` parameter passed to the dump API is `List[torch."
"nn.Module]` or `Tuple[torch.nn.Module]`, module-level names include the "
"index inside the list (`{Module}.{index}.*`). Example: `Module.0.conv1."
"Conv2d.forward.0`."
msgstr ""

